Interface ResponseCallback

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HttpClient, JSONRPCClient

    public interface ResponseCallback
    A callback function to receive a response. This function is passed to make a network request. The response invokes callback methods of this function.
    Author:
    pinaki poddar

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onError(Exception ex)
      Invoked when an error occurred to process a request.
      void onResponse(byte[] bytes, boolean eos)
      Invoked when response is available.

    • Method Detail

      • onResponse

        void onResponse(byte[] bytes,
                boolean eos)
        Invoked when response is available. For streaming response, this can be invoked multiple times to deliver chunks of responses. The end-of-stream is signaled by the boolean parameter.
        Parameters:
        bytes - raw byte data of the response. Never null.
        eos - true indicates end of stream

      • onError

        void onError(Exception ex)
        Invoked when an error occurred to process a request.
        Parameters:
        ex - an exception raised during request processing.
